hed_by`, for example `branch_observed`, `review_observed`,\n    `change_observed`, or `explicit_reference`\n  - `matched_turn_keys`\n  - other observed branch/review/change keys, when present\n- source metadata: agents, providers, models, tool versions\n- latest turn key and latest capture timestamp\n- latest user/assistant excerpts, when cheap to derive\n\nThis command should not hydrate transcript records. It is an index card.\nIt should be sorted by most recent activity first.\n\n### `timeline`\n\nPurpose: answer \"what happened across this session, and which turns look worth\nreading?\"\n\n### Slice 1: Richer `sessions`\n\nGoal: answer \"which related sessions should I inspect first?\"\n\nKeep the existing command shape:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sessions [branch [<branch>] | review <review> | change <change>] [--limit N]\n```\n\nFor targeted lookups:\n\n- sort sessions by latest activity, newest first\n- keep `related_turn_keys`\n- include the requested target and normalized target key\n- expose match evidence as observed target kind, not confidence\n\nFor each session include:\n\n- `session_key`\n- `updated_at`\n- `started_at`, derived from first transcript timestamp when cheap\n- `turn_count`\n- `record_count`\n- `latest_turn_key`\n- `latest_captured_at`\n- source metadata: agent, provider, model, tool version\n- latest user/assistant previews, with provider-internal events avoided or\n  clearly labeled where possible\n- observed branch/review/change targets seen in the related turns\n\nDo not hydrate or return full transcript records from `sessions`.\n\n### Slice 2: Compact `timeline`\n\nGoal: answer \"what happened in this session, and which turns should I read?\"\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T19:27:38.322Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}